Just playing around. :)

A simple Ansible playbook for a 2-node GlusterFS filesystem, based on the
Getting Started guide at 
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/Getting_started_overview

Used a CentOS 6.4 AMI (ami-52009e3b) on Amazon EC2.

- main.yml: Ansible playbook to build the GlusterFS filesystem.
- vars.yml: Variables for configuring the filesystem.
- glusterfs.repo: yum repo for glusterfs.
- create_vol.sh.j2: Script for doing disk partitioning.

